Inflammatory pseudotumor in the liver associated with intrahepatic bile duct stones mimicking malignancy. We describe a 71-year-old man with an inflammatory tumor arising in segment 5 of the liver. The patient was admitted because of acute pain in the right upper quadrant of the abdomen and fever. Initial laboratory tests revealed the following: serum alkaline phosphatase concentration, 634 IU/L serum gamma glutamic transpeptidase concentration, 1,378 IU/L